data.text:
I'm spending the day reading "Caste" by Isabel Wilkerson

“Caste, along with its faithful servant race, is an x-factor in most any American equation, and any answer one might ever come up with to address our current challenges is flawed without it.”

Heading to work. Might I gently suggest that if you are surprised, shocked, or disbelieving of the results thus far, you haven’t taken a hard look at this country and what rights people are willing to sacrifice in exchange for maintaining a caste-based system.
